titlestmt.titleproper: Guide to the City and Regional Planning Collection
titlestmt.author: compiled by Laura Tatum and Sheilah Robinson

publicationstmt.publisher: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on Saturday December 8, 2018 at 11:31

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The collection consists of reports by city, local, and regional planning agencies spanning approximately from 1873 to 2000. The geographic range of the reports is global, but is focused mainly on Southeastern Connecticut and New Haven, though many smaller towns and cities in Connecticut are also represented. More general reports about the New York region and other states, socioeconomic data about the United States, and scattered documentation about urban planning in other countries are also part of this collection.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged in three series: Series I. City Planning Connecticut, 1912-1980. Series II. State and International Planning, 1914-1990. Series III. City Planning Subject Files, 1873-2000, and alphabetically therein.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection consists of reports by city, local, and regional planning agencies spanning approximately from 1873 to 2000. The geographic range of the reports is global, but is focused mainly on Southeastern Connecticut and New Haven, though many smaller towns and cities in Connecticut are also represented. More general reports about the New York region and other states, socioeconomic data about the United States, and scattered documentation about urban planning in other countries are also part of this collection.

Development plans, transportation studies, water resources inventories, park and recreation plans, urban renewal reports, housing market indexes, labor and employment statistics, demographic information, industry and manufacturing data, and planning and zoning reports are included. Of note are a series of reports, "Community Monographs," produced by the Research Division of the Connecticut Development Commission in Hartford. In some instances, these detailed community profiles were collected over a span of many years, which provides insight to the changes in a city or town's development over time.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: City and Regional Planning Collection (MS 1970). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright status for collection materials is unknown. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Transferred from Haas Family Arts Library, 2010.
